        <h2>The Project</h2>
        <p>
          Botsters started from a simple question: how do you give AI agents access to APIs 
          without handing over your credentials?
        </p>
        <p>
          Traditional approachesâ€”environment variables, config files, secret managers with 
          direct accessâ€”all share the same flaw: the agent sees the secret. Once it's in 
          memory, it can be exfiltrated via prompt injection, logged accidentally, or 
          leaked through countless other vectors.
        </p>
        <p>
          SEKSBot takes a different approach: agents never see secrets at all. They request 
          capabilities by name; the broker handles the rest.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="mission-statement">
          Our mission is to facilitate the safe use of highly functional and autonomous agents, 
          using architectural solutions and first principle approaches. As new developments in 
          agentic AI appear, SEKSBot will quickly adapt to provide secure turnkey solutions.
        </p>

